<doc id="48390" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=48390" title="All-Ferrari front row on 2006 Turkish Grand Prix">
<h1>All-Ferrari front row on 2006 Turkish Grand Prix</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=All-Ferrari%20front%20row%20on%202006%20Turkish%20Grand%20Prix&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

Second &lt;a href="w%3AFerrari"&gt;Ferrari&lt;/a&gt; driver &lt;a href="w%3AFelipe%20Massa"&gt;Felipe Massa&lt;/a&gt; won the first place on the &lt;a href="w%3AFIA"&gt;FIA&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3AFormula-1"&gt;Formula-1&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3A2006%20Turkish%20Grand%20Prix"&gt;Turkish Grand Prix&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href="w%3AIstanbul%20Park"&gt;Istanbul Park&lt;/a&gt; racing track. His teammate &lt;a href="w%3AMichael%20Schumacher"&gt;Michael Schumacher&lt;/a&gt; qualified right after him.

&lt;a href="w%3ARenault"&gt;Renault&lt;/a&gt; drivers &lt;a href="w%3AGiancarlo%20Fisichella"&gt;Giancarlo Fisicella&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="w%3AFernando%20Alonso"&gt;Fernando Alonso&lt;/a&gt; managed to get on the second row of the starting grid.

&lt;a href="w%3AJenson%20Button"&gt;Jenson Button&lt;/a&gt;, winner of the previous Grand Prix in &lt;a href="w%3AHungary"&gt;Hungary&lt;/a&gt; was sixth.

&lt;a href="w%3ANick%20Heidfeld"&gt;Nick Heidfeld&lt;/a&gt; had a nice qualification and will start before Button.

&lt;a href="w%3AKimi%20R%C3%A4ikk%C3%B6nen"&gt;Kimi Räikkönen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="w%3ARobert%20Kubica"&gt;Robert Kubica&lt;/a&gt; closed the first eight places on the grid 

