<doc id="48644" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=48644" title="4,400 kilograms of drugs seized in New Delhi">
<h1>4,400 kilograms of drugs seized in New Delhi</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=4%2C400%20kilograms%20of%20drugs%20seized%20in%20New%20Delhi&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

In the biggest ever narcotics haul in &lt;a href="w%3ANew%20Delhi"&gt;India's capital&lt;/a&gt;, the New Delhi police have seized over 4,400 kg of &lt;a href="w%3AMandrax"&gt;Mandrax&lt;/a&gt; and Rs. 20 &lt;a href="w%3Acrore"&gt;crore&lt;/a&gt; from a dealer in the city. The consignment, meant for a customer in the U.S, was seized from a godown in Badarpur, near the Delhi-&lt;a href="w%3AHaryana"&gt;Haryana&lt;/a&gt; border. The alleged trafficker, identified as Vinod Sharma, claimed that the contraband was not his and that he had nothing to do with the matter. Sharma started his career as a scrap-dealer in Delhi, and police suspect that with the help of some contacts he used container depots for drug-trafficking, whilst successfully dodging both the police and the Customs Department.

On Sunday the Delhi Police arrested him at his Kalkaji residence. The Deputy Commissioner of Police for South District, Delhi Police, Anil Shukla said, "Sharma befriended container drivers and once they had driven past customs, he and his men would meet them at a distance and pilfer the containers."

