<doc id="48679" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=48679" title="BC man is selling the boat from old TV series Gilligan's Island">
<h1>BC man is selling the boat from old TV series Gilligan's Island</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=BC%20man%20is%20selling%20the%20boat%20from%20old%20TV%20series%20Gilligan%27s%20Island&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 
A man named George Schultz in &lt;a href="w%3AParksville%2C%20British%20Columbia"&gt;Parksville, British Columbia&lt;/a&gt; is selling the boat from old TV series &lt;a href="w%3AGilligan%27s%20Island"&gt;Gilligan's Island&lt;/a&gt; at the cost of $99,000. The cruiser, originally cost about $290,000 in the 1960s.

"There have been a couple of modifications, so it doesn't look exactly like the original," said Shultz, a boat broker who's selling the 36-foot Wheeler Express Cruiser for fellow Parksdale resident Scotty Taylor. "But it's still the original boat."
Originally, the boat's name was The Blue Jacket. 

"Just for the show, for a stage name, it was called the S.S. Minnow," Shultz said. The name was a reference to &lt;a href="w%3ANewton%20Minnow"&gt;Newton Minnow&lt;/a&gt;, once chairman of the &lt;a href="w%3AFCC"&gt;FCC&lt;/a&gt;.

"He just liked the boat, he wanted to restore it, it was a nice looking boat, a wooden boat, a classic and he likes classic boats," said Shultz. "The hole in the hull was actually the least of the repairs - the interior needed a lot more work". 

Someone later stole the plaque on the boat, but the 46-year-old boat still has the round life preserver with S.S. Minnow emblazoned on it and the skipper's chair.

<h2>Sources</h2>
<ul>
BULLET::::- Todd Battis. "&lt;a href="http%3A//www.ctv.ca/servlet/ArticleNews/story/CTVNews/20060828/minnow_060828/20060828%3Fhub%3DCanada"&gt;B.C. man selling Gilligan's original S.S. Minnow&lt;/a&gt;" — &lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="interwiki-link-foreign"&gt;&lt;a href="w%3ACTV"&gt;CTV&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/i&gt;, August 28, 2006

</ul>
<ul>
