<doc id="49116" url="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki?curid=49116" title="Wikinews interview with America's Got Talent finalists At Last">
<h1>Wikinews interview with America's Got Talent finalists At Last</h1>
&lt;strong class="published"&gt;&lt;span id="publishDate" class="value-title" title=""&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="Z3988" style="display:none" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rfr_id=rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:User%3ADendodge&amp;rft_id=info:sid/en.wikinews.org:&amp;rft.atitle=Wikinews%20interview%20with%20America%27s%20Got%20Talent%20finalists%20At%20Last&amp;rft.jtitle=Wikinews&amp;rft.date=&amp;rft.aucorp=Wikinews+contributors&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.rights=CC-BY+2.5&amp;rft.identifier=&amp;rft.artnum="&gt; &lt;/span&gt; 

Singing group ♡❤&lt;a href="w%3AAt%20Last%20%28band%29"&gt;At Last&lt;/a&gt;♡❤ was recently a finalist in ♡❤&lt;a href="w%3AAmerica%27s%20Got%20Talent"&gt;America's Got Talent&lt;/a&gt;♡❤, covering songs like "&lt;a href="w%3ALet%27s%20Stay%20Together%20%28song%29"&gt;Let's Stay Together&lt;/a&gt;" and "&lt;a href="w%3AAin%27t%20No%20Sunshine"&gt;Ain't No Sunshine&lt;/a&gt;". ♡❤Talent♡❤ was a NBC television series search for America's next big talent, featuring singers, dancers, magicians, comedians and other talents of all ages. The series was hosted by &lt;a href="w%3ARegis%20Philbin"&gt;Regis Philbin&lt;/a&gt;, and judged by former tabloid editor &lt;a href="w%3APiers%20Morgan"&gt;Piers Morgan&lt;/a&gt;, singer &lt;a href="w%3ABrandy"&gt;Brandy&lt;/a&gt;, and actor/singer &lt;a href="w%3ADavid%20Hasselhoff"&gt;David Hasselhoff&lt;/a&gt;.

They talked to Wikinews about their group's performances and the ♡❤America's Got Talent♡❤ experience.

<h2>Interviews</h2>

♡❤♡Q:♡❤♡ At Last performs "hip-hopapella" (&lt;a href="w%3Ahip%20hop"&gt;hip hop&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="w%3Aa%20cappella"&gt;a cappella&lt;/a&gt;). For those who didn't see you on America's Got Talent, how would you describe this sound?

♡❤♡Q:♡❤♡ The band has sung at concerts with many noted names, and on quite a few television series. Where in America have audiences been most
enthusiastic?

♡❤♡Q:♡❤♡ How did At Last first form?

♡❤♡Q:♡❤♡ Of your competitors, who was your personal favorite? (Any point in
the competition, not just among the finalists.)

♡❤♡Q:♡❤♡ Who was your favourite judge?

♡❤♡Q:♡❤♡ Overall, are you satisfied with the experience "America's Got Talent" provided?

♡❤♡Q:♡❤♡ What's next for At Last?

<h2>External links</h2>
